page.title: 11Macclesfield Forest - Flora
page.content:
{Flora}- Along with those listed as being found in the Churchyard, the following varieties of wild flowers can also be found in the surrounding area:
Red Dead Nettle, Tormentil, Chickweed, Mountain Pansy, Wild Pansy, Harebell, Coltsfoot, Thistle, Creeping Buttercup, Dandelion, Foxglove, Rosebay Willowherb, Pale Willowherb, Ground Elder, Bell Heather, Common Bird's-foot Trefoil, Groundsel, Gorse, Shepherd's Purse, Common Mouse-ear, Lady's Smock, Poppy, Hairy Bittercress, Bramble, Hawthorn, Rowan, Wild Cherry, Bluebell, Primrose, Forget-me-not, Honeysuckle, Scabious.
